    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Diamond Logic&#174; Engine Brake -
        Exploded View and Description
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Exploded View and Description</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <figure id="f3350008211" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figK11/K11016.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px" box="no"/>
                <caption>High-pressure oil manifold (brake)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Brake Control Pressure (BCP) sensor</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Brake Shut-off Valve (BSV) assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 plug</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Injection Control Pressure (ICP) sensor</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 90 bolt (12)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M12 plug</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rail end plug assembly (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Injector oil inlet adaptor (6)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Back-up ring (6)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Injector oil inlet seal (6)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure oil manifold (brake)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil inlet O-ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Brake actuator piston (6)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pressure relief valve</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Brake actuator piston lock nut (6)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The engine brake system uses high-pressure oil in the high-pressure oil manifold, controlled by a
                brake shut-off valve, to force six brake actuator pistons down onto the valve bridges to partially open
                one exhaust valve for each cylinder. The release of combustion chamber compression on the power stroke
                increases engine braking. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_25.xml" xrefid="s0139">Diamond Logic&#174; Brake System</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s0139"/>
                for additional details.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
